            . I watched the prisoner into a clothes-shop. I stopped behind, and found the sheet in the kettle.</p>
               <p>GEORGE BARNLEY. I saw the prisoner in the yard; he took up a blanket, but could not get it into the kettle, he then put the sheet in.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was starving.</p>
